# How Large Language Models (LLMs) Work

## Complete Guide: Basic → Advanced → Interview → Real Projects

If you want to become a **GenAI Engineer**, **AI Engineer**, or prepare for interviews at companies like Google, Microsoft, or startups, understanding how an LLM works is essential.

---

# 1. What is an LLM?

**LLM (Large Language Model)** is an AI model trained on massive amounts of text to understand and generate human language.

Examples:

* [Google Gemini](https://gemini.google.com?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
* [OpenAI ChatGPT](https://chatgpt.com?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
* [Anthropic Claude](https://claude.ai?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
* [Meta Llama](https://www.llama.com?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

LLMs can:

* Answer questions
* Write code
* Translate languages
* Summarize documents
* Generate emails
* Solve programming problems

