# Why are they called "Large"?

Because they contain billions of parameters.

Examples:

```text
1 Billion Parameters

7 Billion Parameters

70 Billion Parameters

100+ Billion Parameters
```

More parameters generally allow the model to learn more complex patterns, though efficiency and training quality also matter.

---

# Training Phases

## 1. Pretraining

The model learns language from massive datasets.

Input:

```text
The sun rises in the
```

Target:

```text
east
```

The model repeatedly predicts missing or next tokens.

---

## 2. Fine-Tuning

The model specializes.

Examples:

```text
Medical AI

Legal AI

Coding AI

Finance AI
```

---

## 3. Alignment

Human feedback improves:

* Helpfulness
* Safety
* Accuracy

---

# Temperature

Controls randomness.

Temperature = 0

```text
More deterministic
```

Temperature = 1

```text
More creative
```

---

# Context Window

This is how much text the model can consider at one time.

Example:

```text
Chat History

+

User Question

+

Document

↓

LLM
```

If the conversation becomes longer than the context window, older content may need to be removed or summarized.

---

# Why LLMs Make Mistakes

Reasons include:

* Limited or outdated knowledge (depending on the model)
* Ambiguous prompts
* Incorrect assumptions
* Lack of required context
* Hallucinations (confidently generating incorrect information)

